      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOUBLE LOU (8) is in terrific form with three wins and a luckless Chariots of Fire fifth from his last four starts at Menangle. Draws wider but has the pace to get across and has won all four times he has raced here. Can keep that perfect record intact. HESITATE (7) has more than 9m to make up on DOUBLE LOU through his last start fourth but draws inside that rival this time and beat him home when fourth in the Chariots of Fire two back. Had kicked off his campaign with a G3 win at Melton last month and was a Eureka placegetter last season. Strikes at 50 per cent at this distance. Big chance. SINALOA (6) was runner-up to flying mare Captains Mistress at Listed level two back then chased her again for a terrific Group 1 third in the Chariots of Fire last start, beating the top two selections home. Can mix it with them again. SEATHESTARS (3) didn't perform to market expectations last time but will be fitter and draws well so may be worth another chance.",
